3000Studios: 
Ionos.com

GitHub Copilot: Great! Here‚Äôs exactly how to connect your Vercel deployment to 3000studios.com using Ionos.com:

---

### 1. Get Vercel DNS Records
- In your Vercel dashboard, under your project‚Äôs ‚ÄúSettings‚Äù ‚Üí ‚ÄúDomains‚Äù, select or add `3000studios.com`.
- Vercel will show you the DNS records you need (usually an A record or CNAME).

---

### 2. Log in to Ionos.com
- Go to [Ionos.com](https://www.ionos.com/) and log in.
- Go to ‚ÄúDomains & SSL‚Äù or ‚ÄúMy Domains‚Äù.

---

### 3. Edit DNS Settings for 3000studios.com
- Find `3000studios.com` in your domain list.
- Click ‚ÄúDNS‚Äù or ‚ÄúManage Domain‚Äù ‚Üí ‚ÄúDNS Settings‚Äù.

---

### 4. Add/Update DNS Records
- **If Vercel gives you an A record:**  
  - Delete any existing A records for `@` (root) and add the new A record from Vercel.
- **If Vercel gives you a CNAME:**  
  - For subdomains (like www), set the CNAME to the value Vercel provides.

**Example (for root domain):**
| Type | Host/Name | Value/Points to         | TTL   |
|------|-----------|------------------------|-------|
| A    | @         | 76.76.21.21 (Vercel)   | 1 hr  |

**Example (for www):**
| Type   | Host/Name | Value/Points to                        | TTL   |
|--------|-----------|----------------------------------------|-------|
| CNAME  | www       | cname.vercel-dns.com (Vercel value)    | 1 hr  |

---

### 5. Save Changes and Wait
- Save your DNS changes.
- DNS propagation can take a few minutes to a few hours.

---

### 6. Verify on Vercel
- In Vercel, the domain status will turn ‚ÄúReady‚Äù when DNS is correct.
- Visit https://3000studios.com to confirm your site is live.

---

**If you want, I can generate the exact DNS records you need if you paste the values Vercel shows for your domain. Let me know if you need a step-by-step with screenshots or have any issues!**

