3000Studios: we already have them saved into our current workspace correct just give me the right thing to import

GitHub Copilot: Yes, you already have the .env.example file in your workspace.  
To import your environment variables into Vercel:

1. Open your actual `.env` file (not .env.example) in your workspace.
2. Copy each key-value pair (e.g., `STRIPE_SECRET_KEY=...`, `PAYPAL_CLIENT_ID=...`).
3. In the Vercel project setup, paste each variable into the ‚ÄúEnvironment Variables‚Äù section.
4. Click ‚ÄúAdd‚Äù for each variable, then continue with deployment.

If you want to bulk import, you can upload your `.env` file directly in the Vercel dashboard (if supported), or paste all lines at once.

Example to paste:
```
STRIPE_SECRET_KEY=sk_test_your_stripe_secret_key
STRIPE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=pk_test_your_stripe_publishable_key
PAYPAL_CLIENT_ID=your_paypal_client_id
PAYPAL_SECRET=your_paypal_secret
NEXT_PUBLIC_SITE_URL=https://3000studios-next.vercel.app
NEXT_PUBLIC_VERCEL_ENV=production
```

Just copy your actual values from your `.env` file and paste them into Vercel‚Äôs environment variable manager.

