3000Studios: whats my remote root directory 

GitHub Copilot: Your remote root directory on Vercel is the base directory of your deployed project‚Äîtypically the top-level folder of your Git repository (e.g., `3000studios-next`).  
All files and folders (including .env.local) should be at this root unless you specify a different build directory in Vercel settings.

For your project, the remote root directory is:
```
/
```
or, more specifically:
```
/3000studios-next
```
This is where Vercel expects your package.json, Next.js config, and environment files.

If you use monorepo or custom build settings, you can set a different root in the Vercel dashboard under ‚ÄúProject Settings‚Äù ‚Üí ‚ÄúRoot Directory.‚Äù For your current setup, use the top-level of your repo.

