3000Studios: can we reset the settings without disconnecting the domain

GitHub Copilot: You can reset most Vercel project settings (build, environment, integrations) without disconnecting your domain. Here‚Äôs how:

1. Delete the project in Vercel and re-import it from GitHub‚Äîthis resets all build and integration settings, but you‚Äôll need to re-add your environment variables and domain.
2. If you want to keep your domain connected:
   - Remove the project, then immediately re-import it with the same name.
   - After redeploying, go to ‚ÄúDomains‚Äù in the new project and re-add your custom domain (it will not be lost, just needs to be re-associated).

**Your domain registration is not deleted**‚Äîyou just need to re-link it to the new project instance.

If you want to avoid any downtime, you can:
- Add a temporary placeholder project to the domain, then switch back after reset.
- Or, contact Vercel support and ask them to clear the build cache and hidden integrations for your project, keeping the domain attached.

