‚≠ê MODULE 11 ‚Äî PART 2
Password Hashing + Secure Store (Server Only)

We create a secure KV entry for your password.

File: lib/matrix/auth.ts
import bcrypt from "bcryptjs";
import { kv } from "@vercel/kv";

export async function initMasterPassword() {
  const stored = await kv.get("matrix-password");

  if (!stored) {
    const hash = await bcrypt.hash("Bossman3000!!!", 12);
    await kv.set("matrix-password", hash);
  }
}

export async function validateLogin(pass: string) {
  const hash = await kv.get("matrix-password");
  return await bcrypt.compare(pass, hash);
}


This:

‚úî Stores your password hashed
‚úî Uses industry-standard hashing
‚úî Never stores plaintext
‚úî Resists brute-force attacks

‚≠ê MODULE 11 ‚Äî PART 3
