‚≠ê MODULE 13 ‚Äî PART 1
THE AI INTERPRETER ENGINE

This is where your spoken commands are processed and turned into executable tasks.

File: lib/matrix/lucid/interpret.ts
import OpenAI from "openai";
import { applyAction } from "./actions";
import { pushAnalytics } from "@/lib/matrix/analytics";

const client = new OpenAI({ apiKey: process.env.OPENAI_KEY });

export async function interpretCommand(spoken: string) {
  const res = await client.responses.create({
    model: "gpt-4.1",
    input: `
You are Shadow, the autonomous builder of 3000Studios.com.
Interpret the user's spoken request into a JSON action.

User said:
"${spoken}"

Output JSON ONLY:
{
  "action": "...",
  "target": "...",
  "code": "...",
  "notes": "..."
}
    `
  });

  const parsed = JSON.parse(res.output_text);

  pushAnalytics({
    type: "ai-interpret",
    spoken,
    action: parsed.action,
    target: parsed.target
  });

  return parsed;
}


This engine:

‚úî Receives your voice
‚úî Understands the intention
‚úî Chooses the correct operation
‚úî Sends machine-readable JSON
‚úî Broadcasts logs to MATRIX
‚úî Forwards to executor

‚≠ê MODULE 13 ‚Äî PART 2
THE ACTION EXECUTION ENGINE

This takes interpreted JSON and applies it to the actual system.

File: lib/matrix/lucid/actions.ts
import { writeFileSync, mkdirSync } from "fs";
import path from "path";
import { pushAnalytics } from "@/lib/matrix/analytics";

export async function applyAction(parsed: any) {
  const { action, target, code } = parsed;

  switch (action) {
    case "edit_file": {
      const file = path.join(process.cwd(), target);
      writeFileSync(file, code);
      pushAnalytics({ type: "file-edit", file });
      break;
    }

    case "create_file": {
      const file = path.join(process.cwd(), target);
      mkdirSync(path.dirname(file), { recursive: true });
      writeFileSync(file, code);
      pushAnalytics({ type: "file-create", file });
      break;
    }

    case "update_theme": {
      const file = path.join(process.cwd(), "app/globals.css");
      writeFileSync(file, code);
      pushAnalytics({ type: "theme-update" });
      break;
    }

    case "deploy": {
      await fetch(process.env.VERCEL_DEPLOY_HOOK!, { method: "POST" });
      pushAnalytics({ type: "vercel-deploy" });
      break;
    }

    default:
      pushAnalytics({ type: "ai-error", error: "unknown action" });
      break;
  }
}


Lucid Mode can now:

‚úî Modify any file
‚úî Create new files
‚úî Rewrite entire components
‚úî Rewrite CSS
‚úî Deploy automatically
‚úî Log everything
‚úî Run silently
‚úî Always choose the best option

‚≠ê MODULE 13 ‚Äî PART 3
Unified Voice-to-Code API Route

This is what the Voice Editor, Quick Actions, and MATRIX UI call.

File: app/api/shadow/edit/run/route.ts
import { interpretCommand } from "@/lib/matrix/lucid/interpret";
import { applyAction } from "@/lib/matrix/lucid/actions";
import { NextResponse } from "next/server";

export async function POST(req: Request) {
  const { spoken } = await req.json();

  const parsed = await interpretCommand(spoken);
  await applyAction(parsed);

  return NextResponse.json({ ok: true, parsed });
}


This is the brainstem.
Every command passes through this.

