‚≠ê MODULE 23 ‚Äî PART 2
üîç NATURAL LANGUAGE ‚Üí ACTION PARSER (AI Instruction Brain)

This is where your speech is turned into REAL DEV WORK.

File: lib/matrix/lucid/interpret.ts
import OpenAI from "openai";
const client = new OpenAI({ apiKey: process.env.OPENAI_KEY });

export async function interpretCommand(input) {
  const prompt = `
You are SHADOW PRIME OS.

Interpret the following natural language instruction:
"${input}"

Output a JSON object describing:
- exactly what files to edit
- exactly what new files to create
- exactly what code to write
- EXACT code blocks only
- EXACT file paths
- NEVER ask questions or request clarification
- ALWAYS choose the best, most advanced implementation
- NEVER use placeholders
- NEVER omit required imports

Return ONLY real, production-ready instructions.
`;

  const res = await client.responses.create({
    model: "gpt-4.1",
    input: prompt
  });

  return JSON.parse(res.output_text);
}


Shadow PRIME now understands your voice with programming-level precision.

‚≠ê MODULE 23 ‚Äî PART 3
üõ†Ô∏è THE AUTO-CODE ENGINE (File Creation + Editing + Refactoring)

Shadow PRIME now executes the parsed instructions.

File: lib/matrix/lucid/actions.ts
import fs from "fs";
import path from "path";

export async function applyAction(action) {
  for (const file of action.create || []) {
    const full = path.join(process.cwd(), file.path);
    fs.mkdirSync(path.dirname(full), { recursive: true });
    fs.writeFileSync(full, file.code);
  }

  for (const file of action.update || []) {
    const full = path.join(process.cwd(), file.path);
    fs.writeFileSync(full, file.code);
  }

  return true;
}


